dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset contains the geometries of administrative units globally at level 0 created by MAP in 2018.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
This is an updated version of MAP Admin2013 and is based on a number of sources, includingGlobal Administrative Unit Layers (GAUL), Global Administrative Areas (GADM), and a number of country-specific datasets(see the attribute tables and credits below for full list of sources, and the separate metadata for more detailed information).

Overview:

The MAP Admin2013 admin0 level boundaries have been preserved in this dataset. Where subnational units have been found to be out-of-date and better geometries have been aquired, these have been added to the dataset and made to align to the admin0 boundaries by removing gaps and overlaps, thereby producing a topologically correct dataset. Admin0 is complete globally, but lower levels will only be populated for malaria-endemic countries, where available. If geometries are not available at a given admin level, the geometries of the parent admin level for that country have been included, but all units have been given a name of "Administrative unit not available" and an ID of 0. Attributes of parent units have been included at all levels, so that hierarchies can be determined.

The 'ID' attribute fields are populated with the relevant unique fdef_id from the MAP database. The 'Code' fields are populated with values dependent on their source. For instance,it will be a GAUL code ifa source of "GAUL" is given, if the source is a country's MOH it may be a health unit code, etc, or these may be empty if the source has not provided any codes. The 'Type'fields arepopulated with the name of the admin unit type, according to the given source (e.g. State, City, Health Distritct). This column can also be used to filter out areas that are not administrative units (e.g. Water Body and Salt Flats)and Disputed Territories.

  • The dataset includes:

  • Admin0 – Country

  • Admin1 – Subnational e.g. State/Province(where available)

  • Admin2 – Lower subnational e.g. District/County (where available)

  • Admin3 - Lower subnational e.g. Ward/Village(where available)

Note: if a source of "MAP Admin 2013"is given, the source will be the same as it was in that dataset (i.e. either GUAL 2012 or country-specific MOH datasets),
